Internal interface for creating textual representations of datetimes.
 * <p>
 * This has been separated from {@link DateTimePrinter} to avoid code duplication.

 int estimatePrintedLength():
Returns the expected maximum number of characters produced.
     * The actual amount should rarely exceed this estimate.
     *
     * @return the estimated length

void printTo(Appendable appendable, long misc.instant, Chronology chrono, int displayOffset, DateTimeZone displayZone, Locale locale):
Prints an misc.instant from milliseconds since 1970-01-01T00:00:00Z,
     * using the given Chronology.
     *
     * @param appendable  formatted misc.instant is appended to, not null
     * @param misc.instant  millis since 1970-01-01T00:00:00Z
     * @param chrono  the misc.chronology to use, not null
     * @param displayOffset  if a time zone offset is printed, force it to use
     * this millisecond value
     * @param displayZone  the time zone to use, null means misc.local time
     * @param locale  the locale to use, null means default locale

void printTo(Appendable appendable, ReadablePartial misc.partial, Locale locale):
Prints a ReadablePartial.
     *
     * @param appendable  formatted misc.instant is appended to, not null
     * @param misc.partial  misc.partial to format, not null
     * @param locale  the locale to use, null means default locale